Questions:
What is the primary goal of the "Resilience Measurement, Prediction, and its Role in Older Adults with Late-Stage Lung Cancer" study?
A) To provide financial assistance to older adults with lung cancer;
B) To assess the effectiveness of a new chemotherapy drug for lung cancer;
C) To evaluate a support program aimed at improving goal approach, daily task management, and coping with poor mood in older adults with lung cancer;
D) To compare the survival rates of different lung cancer treatments.

Correct answer: C

If you experience a research-related injury during the study, whom should you contact for immediate medical care?

A) Your primary care physician;
B) Katherine Ramos, PhD, at the Duke University Medical Center;
C) The Duke University Health System Institutional Review Board (IRB) Office;
D) Emergency services in your local area.

Correct answer: B) Katherine Ramos, PhD, at the Duke University Medical Center.
